summary.para: This class is available in Office 2007 and above.
When the object is serialized out as xml, it's qualified name is a:hslClr.

remarks.format:
## Remarks [!INCLUDE[openxmlnoticeiso](~/includes/openxmlnoticeiso.md)] **hslClr (Hue, Saturation, Luminance Color Model)** This element specifies a color using the HSL color model. A perceptual gamma of 2.2 is assumed. Hue refers to the dominant wavelength of color, saturation refers to the purity of its hue, and luminance refers to its lightness or darkness. As with all colors, colors defined with the HSL color model can have color transforms applied to it.
